pr_body: As discussed with @joernu76  in this PR. I have added a new button to store all the current widgets open. So, on clicking the button the  `store_operation_data()` method using the `topLevelWidgets()` gets all the widgets which match the `allowed_widget_names = ["TopViewWindow", "SideViewWindow", "TableViewWindow", "LinearViewWindow"]` and its children `QComboBox` & `QCheckBox`  object along with its current state and stores it in a .txt file at /.config/msui.
